tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  condition_name VARCHAR(50),
  metric_name VARCHAR(50),
  metric_value FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE experiment_conditions (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    condition_name VARCHAR(255),
    startTime TIMESTAMP,
    endTime TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    metric_name VARCHAR(255),
    metric_value DOUBLE,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiment_conditions(experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    condition_id INT,
    result_value TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES performance_metrics(experiment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (condition_id) REFERENCES experiment_conditions(condition_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    metric_id INT,
    value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (metric_id) REFERENCES metrics(metric_id)
);
